The Row Bar by Tamura's is pretty niceand out in the open. It wasn't too busy during lunch time. The service was fast, staff was friendly and helpful. The lunch menu is affordable, the only expensive item on the menu is the garlic chives ribeye steak @$18.00. Alot of seating at the bar and chairs/tables to sit and enjoy company and lunch. 4 Tv's on each corner facing the bar. Come on out and check them out!

Adjacent to M nightclub, the Row Bar is a great spot to come after work, have drinks and watch the game. Very low key, no muss, no fuss. A comfortable spot t relax and unwind. I was just here recently and they just launched a new food menu. The burger was a. ma. zing. Out of this world. The bartender, Scott, was friendly and efficient. The beer selection was great.  I highly recommend the Row Bar! I'll definitely be coming back soon.

I absolutely LOVE this place!  I rarely dish out 5 star reviews but this one is well deserved.  I used to be a regular when this place was Bambuu Bar for several years and I loved the space back then.  I was sad to see Bambuu's close, but the Row Bar took this space and made it even better.  Because it has a roof covering the open space it doesn't even need to be particularly nice outside and this is the place to go anytime of the day. The Row Bar has 4 TVS so that you can catch all of the games and is encourages Cigar smoking customers to come and smoke and drink whiskey.  Once you find the Row Bar you'll see what all the fuss is about.  Very open, comfortable space outside.  A very diverse crowd always makes for interesting people watching.  They make great drinks and have a decent beer selection as well.  I've always had prompt, friendly service as well.  I highly recommend The Row Bar for anyone that likes having a good drink in the "great outdoors" in Honolulu!
The Row Bar has one of the best happy hour offerings in Honolulu, a great outdoor bar, to enjoy cocktails and pupus, watch sporting events and catch live entertainment daily!
